  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic implant wear simulation credibility assessment (NC-4 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA-based polyethylene wear prediction of a total knee replacement (TKR) tibial insert under physiological gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational wear model can identify worst-case contact stress and volumetric wear conditions for a Class II orthopedic device at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment: all factors either assessed at or above required level or formally scoped out with documented rationale. This is a negative-control (clean) package; no weakener should fire.",
